[codex] ### I.10 Robustness one-liner
[codex] Pattern: `These results were robust to controlling for participant demographics (Appendix Table SX).`
[codex] Or the longer form: `These results were robust to several alternative specifications, including controlling for participant gender, race, and age, and analyzing our data with logistic regression (see Appendix Table SX for robustness checks).`
[codex] 
[codex] Studies 1 and 3B have it. Study 2 does not (likely small N + field constraints). Studies 3A, 4A, 4B, 5 should include the short form unless the source omits it.
[codex] 
[codex] ### I.11 DV phrasing ΓÇö preserve verb object always
[codex] Katy red line #5 (Screenshot 5). Whenever a percentage is reported, keep the verb object: `X.X% chose a woman`, `X.X% chose a racial minority author`, `X.X% chose a biopic with a woman protagonist`. NEVER drop the object even when the DV is named elsewhere in the same paragraph.
