[codex] ### I.15 Decimal and notation conventions
[codex] - Sample sizes: comma-separated thousands, e.g., `1,000 participants` (Study 1) but bare `302 participants` (Study 2).
[codex] - Percentages: 1-2 decimals where the source has them (`46.1%`, `25.2%`). Don't add decimals not in source.
[codex] - t/F/z: as the source reports them.
[codex] - p-values: `.010`, `.314`, `< .001` (strict less-than). Three decimals when meaningful; `< .001` when extremely small.
