[codex] As shown in Figure S2A and Table S3 (Models 5-8), the effect of assignment to the race feedback condition on subsequent selection of a racial-minority protagonist was significantly larger than the effects of assignment to receive descriptive feedback about each of the three comparison attributes (all pΓÇÖs Γëñ .009; see Table 2 (cross-study consolidation) for cross-study estimates and Wald tests).
